{
  "texts": [
    "Authors in Ferrag and Maglaras (2019) present an energy framework for smart grids, combining BC technology and EI.",
    "It provides a peer-to-peer energy trading system, that is complemented with an intrusion detection block based on RNNs.",
    "The work in Hasanaj et al. (2021) proposes a solution to train deepfake detection models cooperatively on the edge, with the goal of evaluating time-computing efficiency.",
    "Finally, a memory-efficient DL-based deepfake detection method deployed in the IoT is explained in Mitra et al. (2021).",
    "Their aim is to detect highly sophisticated GAN generated deepfake images at the edge, reducing training and inference time while achieving a certain accuracy."
  ]
}